@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirement"
@prev "Distribution"


 Introduction:

  WordFax is an arexx script that will enable you to write and send
  faxes from WordWorth using GPFax.
  It will let you to activate, or deactivate, the GPFax printer
  driver. Also it will let you to run or quit GPFax.
@endnode

@node "Requirement" "Requirement"
@next "Installing"
@prev "Introduction"


 Requirement:

  RexxMast running. WordWorth6 (way work with earlier versions) and
  GPFax installed somewhere. You should have an assignment to GPFax:

  assign GPFax: DHx:.../GPFax
@endnode

@node "Installing" "Installing"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Requirement"


 Installing:

  This is quite simple. Copy WordFax.rexx to WordWorth:WwArexx/ . And then
  add the script in WordWorth. Choose 'Arexx script' in the tools menu and
  then add.

  Thats it!
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "History"
@prev "Installing"


 Usage:

  @{fg highlight}So, how do we use this thing ?@{fg text}

  @{u}Installing GPFax driver:@{uu}

  When the script is executed it will ask you if you want to use the usual
  printer driver (remove GPFax driver) or the GPFax driver.

  If you selected GPFax driver, the script will check if GPFax is running.
  If not you will be presented with another requester asking if you want to
  run it, or abort.

  Next, you will be given the choise to alter the default company name.
  Now you can type a new name, use the default or abort.

 @{b} NOTE@{ub}: The company name is used in the fax header printed at the
        top of each page.

  Now, to transfer the document to GPFax just select print, and your
  document will be converted to a fax. The fax can either be saved, or sent
  immediately.
  You should also select a density in print setup. Set the density to 6 to
  turn on Fine mode in GPFax.


  @{u}Removing GPFax driver@{uu}:

  Start the script and choose to remove GPFax driver.
  The script will also ask you if you want to quit GPFax. This is not
  necessery if you only want to toggle between the usual printer driver
  and the GPFax driver.


  @{b}@{fg highlight}Thats it, I hope.@{ub}@{fg text}
@endnode

